You are here: 

Integrate and Prepare Data for Analysis
Use CRM Analytics lenses and dashboards to analyze your data. Load, clean, and transform the data into datasets to prepare it for analysis.
The data manager is where you monitor your data jobs, prepare datasets with recipes and dataflows, and connect to data.

Get Started with Data Integration
Data integration involves gathering and preparing Salesforce and external data for analysis. Prepare integrated data into datasets through CRM Analytics lenses and dashboards.

Connect and Sync Your Data to CRM Analytics
Use connectors to access internal and external data sources.
Clean, Transform, and Load Data with Data Prep
Use a visual interface to build recipes that prepare data and load it into a target.
Manage Recipes
Edit and delete created recipes.
Run Data Sync and Recipes to Create and Refresh Datasets
Set up CRM Analytics to load and update data.

Other Ways to Integrate Data
Dataflows and recipes can integrate most data sources. Additional ways include importing CSV or Excel files, or creating a dataset based on snapshots of Salesforce report data.

Get Started Faster with Data Templates
Use purpose-built data templates for common use case data tasks.
Manage Datasets
Edit a dataset to update its data, metadata, row-level security, or restore it to a previous version.

Data Integration Best Practices
Review tips to improve recipe performance and streamline data sync.
Data Integration Troubleshooting
Use tips to resolve problems with data integration issues.
title: Integrating and Preparing Data for Analysis
